    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>For Immigrants, Next Stop Iowa?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Simcox letter says Iowa would have less need to recruit immigrants (Aug 28 article) if its employers paid wages that would allow Iowans to live there; cartoon</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Short of People, Iowa Seeks to Be Ellis Island of Midwest'' (front page, Aug. 28):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Short of People, Iowa Seeks to Be Ellis Island of Midwest'' (front page, Aug. 28):</p>
        <p>Those of us who are natives of Iowa know that Iowa is hardly underpopulated. According to the 1990 census, Iowa had a population of almost 2.8 million, and it is growing.</p>
        <p>We need more public discussion and a return to democracy on questions relating to immigration. In the meantime, it would help if Iowa companies began paying living wages, making it more possible for Iowa natives to be employed there.</p>
        <p>JOHN SIMCOX  Minneapolis, Aug. 31, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
